definition.value: An alkanesulfonic acid that is propane-1-sulfonic acid substituted by sulfanyl groups at positions 2 and 3.

A biflavonoid that is obtained by oxidative coupling of two molecules of  apigenin resulting in a bond between positions C-3 of the hydroxyphenyl ring and C-6 of the chromene ring. Isolated from Thuja orientalis and Rhus succedanea it exhibits antioxidant, cytotoxic and anti-hepatitis B activity.
An alkane that is decane substituted by a methyl group at positions 2,6 and 8. It is a combustion product of natural gas.
A secondary alcohol that is heptane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.
A 2-octene in which the double bond adopts a cis-configuration.
A 2-octene in which the double bond adopts a trans-configuration.
An N-substituted cadaverine that is cadaverine in which one of the amino groups has been converted to the corresponding acetamide.

A diester that is isooctane (2,2,4-trimethylpentane) in which two of the hydrogens (positions not specified) have been replaced by butyryloxy groups. Tentatively identified in human saliva and previously found on human skin.
A quinoline alkaloid that is furo[2,3-b]quinoline substituted by a methoxy and a hydroxy group at positions 4 and 8 respectively.
A member of the class of dithiocarbamic acids that is carbamic acid in which the oxo and hydroxy groups have been replaced by a thiocarbonyl and thiol group, respectively.
